fields.description:
Setting					Current (C01)			Recommended 	Best for Face Recognition				Reason
Resolution				3840x2160 (4K)					✅ Keep 3840x2160								High resolution helps capture face details.
Frame Rate				8 fps							➡️ Set to 10–12 fps								8 is OK, but 10–12 gives better smoothness for detection without too much load.
Bitrate Type			Variable						➡️ Constant (if possible)						Constant bitrate gives more stable quality for frames, important for face clarity.
Max Bitrate				2048 kbps						➡️ 4096–6144 kbps								Your current 2048 kbps is low for 4K. Faces will be more detailed with 4–6 Mbps.
Encoding				H.264							✅ Keep H.264									Good for compatibility and performance.
H.264+					OFF							✅ Keep OFF									H.264+ is better for bandwidth, but OFF keeps max raw quality (better for recognition).
Profile					Main Profile					➡️ High Profile									"High" Profile improves compression for complex scenes (better faces at same bitrate).
I Frame Interval			50								➡️ Keep 50 or lower (e.g., 30)					50 is fine if fps is low. If you increase fps, lower I-frame interval to 30.
SVC					OFF							✅ Keep OFF									We don't want scalable video coding for face recog.
Smoothing				51								➡️ Lower smoothing (20–30)					Higher smoothing might blur faces. Lower smoothing gives sharper details.

⚡ Better to focus on good 4K streams, clear faces, stable bitrate, and sharp image quality — and let your server handle all detection and recognition.

All "G2" series Hikvision cameras have some built-in AcuSense/FaceCapture AI features, but we ignore them — we just need the pure RTSP stream.

Choose 2.8mm lens for wide classrooms (wider field of view), 4mm if you need tighter view (hallways, front door).

Always configure Constant Bitrate (CBR) and High Profile for best RTSP stream quality.

Topic											Recommendation
Indoor Classroom 								Camera	DS-2CD2787G2-LZS
Deep Learning Face Capture in Camera			Not needed for our project — we use server-based RetinaFace + InsightFace
Stream Focus									Good stable 4K stream with constant bitrate, low compression artifacts
Camera Settings								4K resolution, 10–12 fps, Constant Bitrate 4096–6144 kbps, High Profile

Choose 2.8mm lens for wide classrooms (wider field of view), 4mm if you need tighter view (hallways, front door).

✅ 8MP 4K resolution is excellent for face details
✅ Varifocal models let you zoom and optimize framing on faces
✅ ColorVu models are strong if your environment has variable lighting
